Definition: free from stress or conducive to mental ease
Example: having or affording peace of mind; was settled in a comfortable job, one for which he was well prepared; the comfortable thought that nothing could go wrong; was comfortable in his religious beliefs; she's a comfortable person to be with; she felt comfortable with her fiance's parents
Synonyms: noun, feeling, comfortableness, UNCOMFORTABLE, EASY, free, from, stress, or, conducive, to, mental, ease, having, affording, peace, of, mind, was, settled, in, a, comfortable, job, one, for, which, he, well, prepared, the, thought, that, nothing, could, go, wrong, his, religious, beliefs, she, s, person, be, with, felt, her, fiance, parents
Category: adj.all
